org.modelio.metamodel.uml.infrastructure.properties

Interface DynamicPropertyDefinition.IDynamicPropertyResolver

  • Enclosing interface:
    DynamicPropertyDefinition

    public static interface DynamicPropertyDefinition.IDynamicPropertyResolver
    Implementers of this interface are in charge of storing/loading property values.

    Usage :

    • instanciate a property resolver
    • register it at metamodel level through MMetamodelFragment#addDynamicBehavior(String, Object)
    • on your DynamicPropertyDefinition instance, call pdef.setProperty(DynamicPropertyDefinition.PROPERTY_RESOLVER_TABLE, DynamicPropertyDefinition.PROPERTY_RESOLVER_KEY, resolver)

    Since:
    3.8

      • convertToObject

        java.lang.Object convertToObject(DynamicPropertyDefinition pdef,
                                 java.lang.String value,
                                 ModelElement element)
        Convert a value from a string, using the property definition's base type.

        Used after reading a persisted string value in a property table.

        Parameters:
        pdef - definition of the property being edited.
        value - the initial string value. Might be null.
        element - the element this conversion is done for.
        Returns:
        the converted value. Might be null.

                                 java.lang.Object value,

        Convert an object value to string, according to the property definition's base type.

        Used before writing a persisted string value in a property table.

        Parameters:
        pdef - definition of the property being edited.
        value - a value. Might be null.
        object - the element this conversion is done for.
        Returns:
